          "body": "Luke 19 closes the travel narrative that began at 9:51 (\"He resolutely set His face to go to Jerusalem\") and opens Passion Week. Every theme Luke has been developing arrives here: salvation for outsiders (Zaccheus the tax collector), the cost of discipleship and the demand of stewardship (the minas), the kingdom's nature (the entry), and judgment on covenantal unbelief (the lament and the temple). The chapter cannot be read as four loose episodes; it is a single argument about the kind of King who is arriving and the kind of response He demands. Read the chapter as Luke's literary climax — the answer to the question raised in 9:51."
